main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified aerial objects were reported on 17th February 1949 in different locations around Albuquerque, New Mexico, including the observations of elliptical-shaped, larger-than-aircraft objects with varying colors and maneuvers.
interesting points: The observed objects were reported to appear larger than aircraft and exhibited elliptical shapes.
The altitude, direction, and speed of the objects varied among the different reports, indicating dynamic and unconventional flight patterns.
Observers included credible individuals such as professors, military personnel, and civilians, adding legitimacy to the reports.
The objects were observed to emit self-luminous light and did not leave visible trails, leaving some witnesses puzzled by their sudden disappearance.
The weather conditions during the sightings were described as clear with some remaining light in the western sky.
photographs: No photographs present in the report
